body_html:
Same issue here. My version info:
pip3 - 18.1
Python 3.7 (TensorFlow website says it supports up to 3.6)
virtualenv 16.0
Xcode 10 w/ tools

I also tried the following inside and outside virtualenv. "pip3 install tensorflow". I cloned and tried build/install tensorflow using most up-to-date Java, Bazel, six, wheel, numpi, scipy, ect...

I am getting the same exact issues as wildcard.

Running on 2017 MacBookPro 13" Mojave (all software up-to-date).

Pretty sure the issue is Python 3.7. I'm going to try to start a new virtualenv with Python3.6 and try again. I'll keep you updated.
